    • Constructor Detail

      • PlayingGP

        public PlayingGP()
        PlayingGridPane constructor Instantiate earning, set defaut value for pyramidActualStep, cols and rows constraints, define spacings, add nodes and runs the party. If the specified deck does not fit the requirements, it does not run the party and let the user know that there has been a problem with the deck.

    • Method Detail

      • runNewParty

        public void runNewParty(java.lang.String dest)
                 throws EmptyQuestionsListException,
                        DeckUnderFilledException,
                        NotEnoughQuestionsException,
                        TooMuchQuestionsException,
                        ExceedMaxStepsException
        Run a new party using a questions deck.
        Parameters:
        dest - The name of the JSON file used to get the questions deck.
        Throws:
        QuestionsListIsEmptyException - When the questions deck is empty.
        DeckUnderFilledException - When the deck size is lower than the number of steps.
        NotEnoughQuestionsException - When the deck has not enough questions for each round.
        TooMuchQuestionsException - When the deck has too much questions for a round.
        ExceedMaxStepsException - When the actual step is higher than the max steps.
        EmptyQuestionsListException

      • verifyAnswer

        public void verifyAnswer()
                  throws ExceedMaxStepsException
        Verify if the user has either won the party or lost or answered correctly and reacts accordingly.
        Throws:
        ExceedMaxStepsException - When the actual step is higher than the max steps.

      • onRightAnswer

        public void onRightAnswer()
        If the answer is right and the actual step is less than the max step, then it shows to the user that he answered correctly and pause the party for 1.5 seconds. Then go to the next question. If the user has won, it indicates this to him and then stop the timer.

      • onLost

        public void onLost()
        If the user has lost it indicates to him that he lost and the amount of money he won. Then gets the GUI back to the home pane.
